OL,6,F"In reaching our conclusion we
OL,7,Freiterate the need for finality in
OL,8,Fcriminal proceedings, we must deduce
OL,9,Ffrom this appeal that the applicant
OL,10,Fdoes not fully appreciate that.
OL,12,F"What must be self-evident is the
OL,13,Fstress and upset this latest appeal
OL,14,Fattempt will have caused to the
OL,15,Ffamilies of the deceased."
OL,17,FDame Siobhan said the original trial
OL,18,Fjudge had been cited on the issue of
OL,19,FHowell's control of Stewart and he
OL,20,Faltered her sentence accordingly.
