OL,6,FShe concluded: "We find no merit in
OL,7,Fany of the points raised on appeal."
OL,9,FStewart's lawyer, Kevin Winters of KRW
OL,10,FLaw, said: "Today's decision of the
OL,11,FCourt of Appeal to refuse leave is
OL,12,Fdisappointing but in many ways not
OL,13,Funexpected given the very high bar we
OL,14,Fhad to reach to convince the court to
OL,15,Flook at this relatively new issue
OL,16,Fafter so many years."
OL,18,FHe added: "Today's ruling doesn't end
OL,19,Fthe quest for Hazel Stewart to
OL,20,Fhighlight that she was a victim of
OL,21,Fcoercive control.
